%% Data Science Pipelines Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Dashboard
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant API as DSP API Server<br/>8888/TCP HTTP(S)<br/>8887/TCP gRPC
    participant DB as MariaDB<br/>3306/TCP MySQL
    participant S3 as S3 Object Store<br/>9000/TCP or 443/TCP
    participant K8s as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Argo as Argo Workflow Controller
    participant Task as Pipeline Task Pod
    participant PA as Persistence Agent
    participant MLMD as MLMD gRPC Server<br/>8080/TCP gRPC

    Note over User,S3: Flow 1: Pipeline Submission (External User)
    User->>Router: POST /apis/v2beta1/pipelines<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS
    Router->>OAuth: Reencrypt TLS<br/>8443/TCP
    OAuth->>API: Forward (proxied)<br/>8888/TCP, TLS (PodToPodTLS)
    API->>DB: Store pipeline metadata<br/>3306/TCP, TLS (configurable)<br/>Auth: DB credentials
    API->>S3: Upload pipeline artifacts<br/>9000 or 443/TCP<br/>Auth: S3 AccessKey/SecretKey
    API-->>OAuth: Pipeline created response
    OAuth-->>Router: HTTPS response
    Router-->>User: JSON Response

    Note over Argo,MLMD: Flow 2: Pipeline Execution (Workflow)
    Argo->>K8s: Create pipeline task pod<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Task->>API: Report status (ml-pipeline)<br/>8888/TCP HTTP(S), TLS (PodToPodTLS)
    Task->>API: gRPC calls<br/>8887/TCP, TLS (PodToPodTLS)
    Task->>MLMD: Log artifacts/executions<br/>8080/TCP gRPC, TLS (PodToPodTLS)
    Task->>S3: Read/Write artifacts<br/>9000 or 443/TCP<br/>Auth: S3 credentials

    Note over PA,K8s: Flow 3: Persistence Agent Sync
    PA->>API: Sync run status<br/>8888/TCP HTTP(S), TLS (PodToPodTLS)
    PA->>K8s: Watch Workflow CRs<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token

    Note over User,DB: Flow 4: Operator Health Checks
    Note right of OAuth: DSPO Controller probes backends
    OAuth->>DB: Health check<br/>3306/TCP MySQL<br/>Auth: DB credentials
    OAuth->>S3: Health check (ListBuckets)<br/>9000 or 443/TCP<br/>Auth: S3 credentials
